      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TUSKEN RAIDER (1) has been out of the placings at his last two outings but shapes well for this if he can recapture his powerful win a few runs back, getting around this track over 407m in 23.55. Hot win three back and looks the one to beat here. AWESOME CAMBLA (2) turned in a plain run last time when seventh at this track over 407m behind Non Stop Tommy (24.48) in a Grade 4. Was in the money prior to that. Can do much better this time. JALAPENO POPPER (8) is racing well without winning, recording three minors on end, the latest when checked in the run and finishing third in a Grade 5/6 at this track (30.93). Harder here but expected to feature again. WANGAROA WALLY (3) was a shock winner last start but don't underestimate.",
